id%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACivil+discourse\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\"><a href=\"/wiki/John_Locke\" title=\"John Locke\">John Locke</a> (1690). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.mnstate.edu/gracyk/courses/web%20publishing/LockeBook3_9.htm\"><i>An Essay Concerning Human Understanding</i></a>. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-14-043482-8\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-14-043482-8\">0-14-043482-8</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=An+Essay+Concerning+Human+Understanding&amp;rft.date=1690&amp;rft.isbn=0-14-043482-8&amp;rft.au=John+Locke&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mnstate.edu%2Fgracyk%2Fcourses%2Fweb%2520publishing%2FLockeBook3_9.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACivil+discourse\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Peter Walmsley (1995). \"Prince Maurice's Rational Parrot: Civil Discourse in Locke's Essay\". <i><a href=\"/wiki/Eighteenth-Century_Studies\" title=\"Eighteenth-Century Studies\">Eighteenth-Century Studies</a></i>. <b>28</b> (4): 413\u2013425.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Eighteenth-Century+Studies&amp;rft.atitle=Prince+Maurice%27s+Rational+Parrot%3A+Civil+Discourse+in+Locke%27s+Essay&amp;rft.volume=28&amp;rft.issue=4&amp;rft.pages=413-425&amp;rft.date=1995&amp;rft.au=Peter+Walmsley&amp;rfr